rComments: Did everything in his power to make the class harder on the students than it needed to be. No use of laptops allowed, only hand written notes. He did not write on the board, have power points or provided lecture notes. He gave no review for either test nor the final exam. Questions on the exam were obscure and did not cover main events or people.

I truly believe he deserves the medal for "worst professor". When it came to the exams Professor Hurst tested the students on the most irrelevant information. He was also VERY unhelpful. You definitely need to have knowledge when it comes to Chinese history BEFORE you attend this class even though it says you don't in the syllabus.

Worst format. Quizzes asked questions about unnecessary knowledge. Little facts that noone needed to know. Final exam was the worst. Overall the class could have been more exciting especially since the topic was China.

Worst professor I have ever had. He would not allow us to use laptops in a two hour lecture, gave the class literally ZERO guidelines for the midterm & final exam (worth 50%), threw whiny temper tantrums if it appeared we did not do all the readings & stopped lecture to stare down any student who arrived late... I could go on and on.
